[{"id":"VR642059","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a diagram of a same spaceship with mass 3 m moving to the left with speed 3 v. The spaceship separates into two pieces. The piece on the left has mass 2 m and is moving to the left with speed 4 v. The piece on the right has mass m and is moving to the left with speed v.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR642059.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A spaceship of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 m\"><math alttext=\"3 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is in deep space, far from any other objects, traveling with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3 v\"><math alttext=\"3 v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn><mi>v</mi></math></span></span> to the left, as shown in the top figure. The spaceship separates into two pieces, with masses <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 m\"><math alttext=\"2 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>, as shown in the bottom figure. The piece with mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 m\"><math alttext=\"2 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> moves to the left with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 v\"><math alttext=\"4 v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>v</mi></math></span></span>. Why does the piece of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> move to the left with speed <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>v</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR642059_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An external force on the system slows down the piece of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An external force on the system increases the speed of the piece of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 m\"><math alttext=\"2 m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no external force on the system so the momentum of the system must remain constant.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is no external force on the system so kinetic energy must remain constant.</p>"],"answer":2}]